NEWS GOV-MO: Alert: Department of Police calls on citizens to be wary of counterfeit text messages from telecommunications companies

Recently, the Japanese police have seized a number of cases of telecommunications fraud, where illegal actors faked that the company sent fraudulent text messages to the owner of the site with a link to a website attached to it, in order to exchange the prize for a bribe as soon as possible.

The owner enters the credit card information and verification code as instructed, and as soon as he receives a notification from a financial institution about the existence of unknown spending records, he suspects that the information has been stolen through the above-mentioned website.
After checking, it is confirmed that the relevant telecommunications company did not send the above text message.

The police department urges citizens to be more vigilant in case of receipt of similar text messages from mobile phones and not to log in to the website containing the text message or provide any personal information; if asked to provide credit card information, account transaction code, or verification code of transactions, be even more careful to prevent the theft of credit cards.
Here are some tips to prevent fraud:
1. Increased attention to cybersecurity information and increased awareness of personal prevention;
2. Avoid casual access to and registration of personal and credit card information on unregistered websites in order to avoid theft;
3. Be vigilant against fake websites and phishing websites, and always check that the website address is in full compliance with the official website;
4. Install and regularly update anti-virus software for mobile phones, mobile devices or computers;
5. In the event of suspicion of fraud or other crimes, call the Police Fraud Enquiry Hotline 8800 7777 or the Reporting Hot Line 993 immediately.
EU summit debates refugee policy, EU officials: Acceptance process stalled step by step
EU summit fights over refugee policy, EU officials: There are bottlenecks every step of the way

At the latest EU summit of the day, EU Commission President Jean-Claude Juncker said EU leaders had agreed to a stricter policy on illegal immigration, which would make it easier to deport illegal migrants, according to AFP news agency.
The EU's move is reportedly in response to growing concerns about illegal immigration in Europe, where the core problem today is the small number of illegal migrants who are ultimately repatriated.
According to the summit document, EU leaders called on the Commission to immediately mobilize large amounts of EU funds to strengthen the external borders through infrastructure and surveillance.
However, the EU is in constant dispute with its member states over issues such as the payment of fence fees.
In the meantime, he has repeatedly said that EU funds will not cover the costs.

However, diplomatic officials from some member states said that if the EU could share parts of the installation of cameras, observation towers and other infrastructure along the external borders, this would help the country's national budgets to speed up the construction process.

EU officials acknowledge that there are bottlenecks at every step of the refugee reception process, limited capacity and the inability of member states' immigration authorities to prevent refugees from filing a myriad of asylum applications in EU countries, and that the EU's system is in near-permanent crisis mode, according to EURACTIV.
According to the European Commission, the EU's Schengen countries received more than 920,000 asylum applications last year, almost half as many as the year before.
Meanwhile, the EU recorded more than 330,000 illegal entries last year.
In this context, the summit also agreed on a guiding principle that EU countries can repatriate illegal migrants on the basis of a court ruling in another member state.
In addition, EU leaders also agreed to increase the use of the concept of a security state, which would pave the way for the EU to develop a common list, the report said.

The E-account of the hedge fund is closed: the Securities and Exchange Commission authorizes the development of all funds in the name of investors to be consolidated and consulted - Economic Observer Network - Professional financial news website
Economic Observer Net Journalist Chen Yue said that the complexity of the fund's purchasing channels makes it difficult to aggregate account information.
Do you always forget your little treasure trove?
These problems of the Kisan people are about to be solved.
On 10 February, the Securities and Exchange Commission (SEC) announced the launch of an open test run of the E-Account APP in mobile app stores.

It is reported that the E-accounting platform provides a one-stop-shop for private investors with information on publicly traded fund accounts and shares, aimed at solving the industry service pain points of many small and medium-sized investors who have forgotten their accounts.
According to Wind data, as of the end of 2022, there are a total of 156 public fund managers in the country, with a fund size of about 26 trillion yuan.
The accounting systems of the participating registries are independent of each other and lack a unified industry inquiry channel.
At the end of 2021, there were more than 720 million fund investors in our country, which means that half of the country invested in fund products.
Previously, investors had to inquire about purchases through different sales agencies, whereas with a hedge fund E-account, you can check all sales channels and have a clear view of the fund.
What is an E-Account APP?

According to the relevant documents, the E-Account APP is a mobile application for the publicly traded fund industry, approved by the Securities and Exchange Commission of China for development and construction, which provides investors with a one-stop-shop inquiry about the holding of off-market shares in all market public fund products.

Investors can easily and quickly control their holdings of the off-the-shelf shares of publicly traded fund products owned by the fund managers purchased through various sales channels throughout the market, improving the efficiency of queries.

Specifically, the information that investors can query through the E-account of the hedge fund includes: information about the fund accounts opened with the managers of public funds in the market; information on the trading accounts open at the public fund sales agencies; and the out-of-the-box holdings of products such as publicly-traded investment funds (PIFs) and collective asset management schemes, which are not limited to 200 people.

The Shanghai Securities Fund Evaluation Research Center's head of business, Liu Yiqiu, told Economic Observation Network reporters that investors can get a one-stop-shop information about all their out-of-the-box IPO fund holdings through the E-Account Coin App, which helps them find forgotten asset tokens, and more importantly, summarize the full account information of the integrated fund investment situation for clients, helping clients to gain a more timely, accurate and complete understanding of their own investments, thereby better optimizing their portfolio fund configuration and better planning their financial arrangements.
How to register?

The reporter noted that at present, the E-Account APP has been launched in mobile app stores such as Huawei, Apple, Xiaomi, OPPO, Vivo, etc., but the app is still in the open trial phase, registration requires filling out an invitation and investors can contact the fund manager who holds the funds to obtain it.

A customer service representative of a large public fund in Shanghai gave a six-digit invitation code to a reporter from Economic Watch and told reporters that during the test phase of the app, China settlement provides a certain number of invitations to each fund manager, and investors come and get them, we will provide them.
After the test run, the invitation code will no longer be used for open user registration.
Oh, my God.

According to the official website of the Securities and Exchange Commission, the journalists downloaded and used the relevant documents to register the account and complete the inquiry. The entire process took only a few minutes and was mainly divided into four steps: user registration, authentication of real name, binding the fund account, and public fund request.

After this step of authentication, click on the button of binding the hedge fund, and all the fund products purchased by the journalist through the various fund sales platforms will be presented in the list of bundling options ("binding accounts"). After completing this link, you can visually see the total assets of the invested fund and start using the query function.
It is worth noting that the E-account is only a consultation service for investors and cannot be used for buying and selling.
The data date displayed in the E-account tab generally moves the user's query date (T-day) forward by three trading days.

For example, if a hedge fund E-account is opened on February 10, the total assets, fund shares, and net worth of the fund shown on the assets page correspond to the date pushed forward by three trading days to that date, which is February 7.

Multiple data recession Taiwan's economy starts the year poorly - Xinhua

Xinhua Taipei, Feb. 11 (Xinhua) -- Taiwan's export trade volume has plummeted five times, the Manufacturing Purchasing Managers Index (PMI) has shrunk for the seventh consecutive month, and the consumer price index (CPI) is in third place... Recently, Taiwan authorities have released economic data for January 2023.
According to analysts, Taiwan's economy started the year off poorly and is under a lot of growth pressure.
According to the Department of Finance, Taiwan's exports in January were $31.51 billion, down 21.2% year on year for the fifth consecutive month.
Exports of 11 major export categories declined in comparison to the same period last year.
Plastic and its derivatives and optical devices suffered the biggest declines, falling by 37.6% and 35.7% respectively.
Electronic parts exports decreased by 20.1% year on year, the largest decrease in 11 years.
Among them, integrated circuits decreased by 18.3% per year, the biggest decline in 14 years.

According to the department's head of statistics, Yumena, this shows that the effects of weak demand in the consumer electronics industry are spreading and the industry is entering a period of correction.
Statistics show that Taiwan's imports and exports doubled in January, with a surplus of only US$2.34 billion, the lowest level in nearly three years.

Taiwanese authorities' finance department believes that global demand for terminals is declining, industrial inventory adjustments are holding back manufacturers' willingness to buy, export growth is unlikely to improve in the short term, and Taiwan's exports are likely to decline higher than expected in Q1 of this year.

The Taiwan Manufacturing Purchasing Managers Index (PMI) was 40.4% seasonally adjusted in January, falling 3.3 percentage points from December last year, a seven-month consecutive contraction, according to the China Institute of Economics in Taiwan.
In the system of economic monitoring indicators, the PMI is a dry line at 50% and an index greater than 50% represents an expansion of the economy and a contraction.
Among the five indicators that make up the January Taiwan PMI, new orders, contraction in production and employment, decreased delivery times for suppliers, and shrinking inventories.

The total number of industries reporting PMI contraction is 35.1%, followed by electron microscopy (35.2%), chemicals (39.2%) and medical technologies (45.7%), basic raw materials (42.4%), transportation industry (46.6%), and food textiles (44.7%).
In terms of prices, the CPI for Taiwan rose by 3.04% in January, breaking the 3% mark since July last year.
Among them, vegetable prices soared 28.25% to a new 17-month high.
The CPI in January and February should be close to the 2.71 percent average in December last year, and inflation pressures are still present and still high.
Looking ahead to this year's Taiwanese economy, experts are pessimistic about reports in the island media, such as the Daily Mail, Yahoo Financial, and others.

Liu Daing, a professor at the Faculty of Economics at Taipei Central University, said that a recession in exports could cause cash flow problems for export manufacturers and increase the risk of debt default.
At the same time, the decrease in orders causes manufacturers to cut human costs, affecting the labor market and the household economy, which in turn affects their purchasing power.

A researcher at the Taiwan Institute of Economic Research, Liu Dajun, believes that inflation in the US and Europe is unresolved this year, demand continues to shrink, and Taiwan's export slump is expected to continue into the first half of the year.
As Taiwan's economy relies heavily on exports and has been hit by a slump in imports, full-year economic growth will be lower than last year.

The first batch of personal pension funds is on sale for a minimum of 360 days - Xinhua
The first personal pension products go on sale
There are seven products available, with a minimum of 360 days.
Personal pension products are finally online.

On February 10, the China Financial Network published the first list of personal pension products, with the official launch of seven personal retirement products from Banking Finance, Farmers Bank Finance and China Post Finance.

Thus, the shelves of individual pension accounts have finally gathered the four categories of products: personal retirement savings, personal pension financing, private pension insurance, and public pension funds.
It is reported that the first batch of personal pension management products are all open-ended net worth products, of which 5 are new products and 2 are long-term products.

According to the Beijing Youth Daily, four of the five newly developed products are all fixed-income products, with a shorter holding period of 365 days, 540 days and 720 days respectively, and an annualized performance of 3.70 percent - 4.20 percent, 4.10 percent-4.60 percent and 4.40 percent to 4.90 and 5.25 to 5.75 percent.

The remaining one new product is Liang Post Bank's Wealth Add-on; Lian Jin holds No. 1 for a minimum of 1,095 days. It is also a fixed-income product. The auction started on February 10 and ended February 19.
Of the two sustainable products, one is only KARAN BANK FINANSIAL SYSTEM, which focuses on 360-days of technological innovation in RMB, with a mixed investment category and a three-level risk rating.

The other long-term product is the Liang Postal Bank's Wealth Add-on. Lian Jin holds the shortest 365 days of No. 1 Liaoning, fixed income type, which began raising on December 30 last year, officially operates on January 4 this year and has a cumulative net worth of 1.0011 as of February 8.

According to the opinion of the State Council Office on Promoting the Development of Individual Pensions, the financial products that can be invested in the funds of an individual pension fund account include banking, savings deposits, commercial pension insurance, public funds, etc.
The sale of the first personal pension fund products marks the official opening of personal retirement fund accounts for private pension investors.
In November last year, the Banking Supervisory Board (BSC) adopted a temporary measure to manage the personal pension business of Commercial Banks and Financial Companies.

The scheme allows participants to purchase personal retirement savings, personal pension management products, individual pension insurance products and products of the Personal Pension Public Fund through their Personal Pensions Fund Account.

Subsequently, the Ministry of Social Affairs, Finance, and the three departments of the National Tax Administration issued notices clarifying the implementation of individual pension systems in Beijing and Tianjin, as well as 36 pioneering cities and regions such as Shijiazhuang, Xi'an New District, Shaanxi Jin City and others.
By the end of 2022, there were 19.54 million individual pensioners and 6.13 million contributors, for a total of 14.2 billion yuan.
Previously, the banks participating in the pilot only offered three types of products: individual retirement savings, individual pension insurance products and individual public pension funds.
Now that personal pension funds are also concentrating, how should investors choose?
According to experts from the R&D department of the Bank, both the pilot and the individual pension products have three characteristics when compared to other personal pensions products.
The first is stability, better risk management mechanisms, more robust investment strategies and concepts, and the implementation of independent third-party custody outside the parent bank.

The second is the long-term, in the pilot phase, the term of pension funds is 5 years or more, and the next phase of the individual pension fund, with a minimum holding period of one year in principle, is encouraged to hold more than three years.
The third is accessibility, the product purchase threshold is low and the starting point is usually 1 yuan, some are as low as 0.01 yuan.
Experts point out that investors should make choices based on product characteristics and their own risk tolerance.

Individual pension savings have the characteristics of a longer term, higher interest rate, high security, and are suitable for people with low risk tolerance; personal pension insurance products are more secured and better suited to people who cannot afford investment risks and can accept stable returns; while individual pension management products and public fund products do not guarantee either the cost or the return, have a certain investment risk, but the expected return is higher, are appropriate for those with certain financial knowledge and a higher ability to take risks.

Chongyang asks what he thinks about the U.S. non-farm employment data in January: over-expectations and future trends - Economic Watch Network - Professional financial news website
Q: How do you see the January non-farm employment data in the US going beyond expectations and future trends?

A: The U.S. Department of Labor released January 2023 data on nonfarm employment, adding 517,000 new jobs, well above the 189,000 expected by the market; the unemployment rate dropped to 3.4%, its lowest level in nearly 50 years; hourly wage growth was 4.4%, relative to the rest of the world, 0.3%, slightly slower.

Overall, there are a number of one-off and technical disruptions to this data, such as teachers returning from strikes, corrections to survey statistics, updates to the seasonal adjustment factor, which may be corrected in the future (reference: January 2022 increase in non-farmers from 5.04 million to 36.4 million), or nonfarm employment is not as strong as the data shows).

Structurally, the impact of layoffs in high-tech companies remains, but at a low level; new jobs in highly exposed services such as leisure hotels, education and healthcare have recovered significantly, and data show that the labor gap in the services sector remains.

Combined with similarly higher-than-expected service PMI, recoveries in job vacancies and labor shortages, and stronger consumer credit data, we assess a rapid recovery in the U.S. service industry after extreme weather and holidays.
We believe that the supply-demand tensions in the US job market are unlikely to improve without a recession.
Currently, there are more than 5 million labor gaps in the U.S. labor market, and labor participation rates are slowly rising, especially among those aged 25-54 who are nearing pre-epidemic highs.
In addition, stronger consumer demand will further delay the impact of austerity on the job market due to the strength of excess savings and consumer credit among U.S. residents.
Continued tight supply and demand in the U.S. job market will be the bedrock of America's economy in 2023.
Overlapping is nearing the end of interest rate hikes, inflation expectations are recurring, and we are not optimistic about the continued decline in wage growth.
hallucination
Prior to the release of the data, the US equity and bond markets were overly optimistic about the Fed's rate hike path.

With inflation data continuing to improve, while the Fed continues to shorten the pace of rate hikes while maintaining the fragile balance of the market's expectations, the markets are turning a blind eye to the biased rhetoric by the Federal Reserve, which not only expects to stop raising rates early, but also to expect two rate cuts at the end of this year.

In the context of tight labour market supply and demand and the uncertain impact of austerity policies, we believe that the Fed's guidance on interest rate hikes at the end of the year is relatively reasonable, and that extreme market expectations of adjustment and trade congestion will cause some damage to the market.

Nevertheless, the persistence of wage growth is difficult to change the current trend of rapid decline in inflation, with the year-on-year turnaround of M2 data and the gradual improvement of the leading indicators of various CPI scores, since October the US CFI data has moved to a rapidly declining phase, while the persistent growth of wages will only serve as a basis for future Inflation data.

Fitness industry needs to get out of crisis of trust - Xinhua
Another big gym with a thunderstorm?
Recently, the issue of the rights of members of well-known gyms has attracted public attention.

After the Spring Festival, many members found that their stores were not functioning normally, and then the rumors about the collapse of the runway caused panic among the members, leading to the intervention of public security and social services.
Finally, the relevant officials of the institution responded by promising to work hard to protect the legitimate rights and interests of their employees and members until the wind died down.
Some of the stores of individual gyms are experiencing operational problems, temporary closures, and consumers should be calm and waiting for the problem to be solved.
Behind the fitness club member advocacy is a deep-seated crisis of confidence in the industry.
Traditional gyms in the country generally adopt a pre-paid model, and the underlying logic behind their development is that users don't get paid.
With cash flow from pre-sale membership cards and the continuous opening of new stores, it seems to be able to cycle back and forth, but in reality it is not possible to form a stable profit model.
Negative information about industries such as gyms and runways is frequently reported, causing a strong shock to consumer confidence.
In terms of market prospects, gyms are certainly a lucrative business.
The gymnasium, despite its ups and downs, has always been the focus of capital.
Several data shows that the market continues to warm up, with the heat rising in areas such as textile consumption.
Specifically to the fitness market, as the standard of living of residents steadily improves, the concept of healthy living is deeply ingrained in people's hearts.
The better the situation, the more the industry needs to pay attention to the quality of development.

However, the individual agencies, blindly optimistic about the recovery of the fitness market after the crisis, have sounded the horn of opening up the country and invested a brain of financing in the construction of new stores.

It is undeniable that in recent years, many institutions have withdrawn from the epidemic, the industry has been rechartered, and strong companies have been selectively increasing their acquisition efforts, repositioning, which is not a new opportunity.
However, in order for the fitness market to develop into a virtuous cycle and move steadily along Kangzhou Avenue, the industry must change the traditional model and change its business strategy.
It is only by staying strong and rebuilding consumer confidence and security that we can truly win the market and the future.
Compared to building new stores to grab the market, the fitness industry currently needs more to focus on optimizing services, with high-quality development to stabilize users.
First of all, it is the service that keeps users.
The gym belongs to the service industry, whose essence is to adhere to a user-oriented approach, closely around the needs of users, focusing on the improvement of service quality.
Secondly, digital transformation will improve the user experience.
For example, the current popular internet gym model allows users to pay for and choose their own venue.
At the same time, body data and movement data can be used effectively to meet social needs, enabling a complete service loop from online to offline.
With no private sales, no huge annual passes, users' worries about the gym's run-ins with the law are reduced, and trust is enhanced.
In addition, it is important to actively explore the multi-industry model.

Nowadays, sports consumption has moved from single-service to scene consumption, and fitness clubs are expected to become the new entry point for consumption and surrounding products such as sports supplements and gym equipment that are needed for fitness or will become new perks, providing consumers with a richer choice.

The Biden administration on Friday (February 10) blacklisted six Chinese entities suspected of involvement in the espionage balloon program.
The U.S. Department of Commerce says the five Chinese companies and one research institute help modernize the Chinese military, especially its aerospace program, which includes shuttles and planes.
Blacklisted companies find it difficult to access technology exports to the United States.

The list is known as the Entity List, and companies on the list will not be able to purchase technology or goods from U.S. suppliers unless they obtain a special export license from the Department of Commerce.

The companies included in the blacklist are: Beijing Nanjiang Aerospace Technology Co., Ltd., China Electronics Technology Group's 48th Research Institute, Dongguan Ling Air Remote Sensing Technology Company, Xiamen Aircraft Technologies Group Limited, Guangzhou Tianhaixiang Air Technology Corporation and Shaanxi Xian Air Force Technologies Company Limited.
In the meantime, the White House has said it is considering broader measures to expose and address larger-scale surveillance activities by China that threaten U.S. national security.
The balloon incident sparked further tensions between China and the United States, and U.S. Secretary of State Blinken canceled a trip to China.

The U.S. dropped the balloon on February 4, and the Chinese government offered serious engagement to the American Embassy in China, criticizing the United States for its severe shock and undermining the efforts and processes of both sides to stabilize Sino-American relations.

Based on the available evidence of the wreckage and information from the Chinese military's procurement platform, the U.S. government concluded that the balloon manufacturer had direct ties to the PLA and was a supplier approved by the military.

In a press conference on Friday, Chinese Foreign Ministry spokesman Mao Zedong said that China had repeatedly explained and clarified its position regarding the accidental entry of a Chinese unmanned aerial vehicle into US airspace due to irresistible force.
According to the State Department's website, she added that the relevant resolutions of the US Congress are purely political manipulation and hype.
The Chinese side strongly disagrees and firmly opposes this move.

Matthew Axelrod, Assistant Secretary for Export Enforcement at the U.S. Department of Commerce, said: "Today's action demonstrates our collective efforts to identify and prevent China from using espionage balloons that violate the airspace of the United States and more than 40 countries".

The Pentagon said the second downed object, which first entered U.S. airspace on Thursday night and was tracked by the US military as it moved over northeastern Alaska, flew at an altitude of 12,000 meters (40,000 feet), was about the size of a small car and much smaller than the Chinese spy balloon that was shot down earlier.
The Pentagon also believes that at this time there is no indication that the object can be manipulated.

White House National Security Council Strategic Communications Coordinator John Coby said on Friday that while it was not clear what the high-flying object looked like, it posed a legitimate threat to the safety of civil aviation aircraft.
According to Kobe, the object is different from the spy balloon found in the United States, as it does not have a suspended pendant carrying a payload.
The best description we can come up with at the moment is that we call it a mythical object mystery, says Kobe.
President Biden listened to the Pentagon's advice before ordering the object to be shot down, and he was very cautious in making the decision, Corby added.
U.S. officials describe the object as being roughly the size of a small car, with no handlebars, no suspension, and flying at an altitude of about 10,000 meters.
But this information still fails to answer basic questions, such as what the object is, what country it belongs to, and what its mission is.
Many online analyses and speculations suggest that this could be another Chinese balloon.
It may have come from China, like the spy balloon that invaded U.S. airspace and the Chinese one hovering over Latin America, both performing a mission in different locations.
Some have also linked the Alaskan flying saucer to a UFO.
The US Newsweek report quoted former US Congressman Peter Meijer as tweeting on Friday that he hoped the UFO was also a spy balloon and not a legitimate UFO.
The irony of Liu confusing spacecraft with weather balloons is surprising, but it doesn't deserve to trigger an interstellar conflict, Liu Meijer said.
Major tweeted shortly after Kobe confirmed that the object in Alaska had been shot down.
According to Newsweek, Major is not the only one who suspects the object is a UFO.

Representative Tim Burchett, a Republican from Tennessee, criticized the government's cover-up last month, demanding that the Office of the Director of National Intelligence (DNI) publish a report on the UFO case.
Northern Exchange financing securities trading business to start next week - Xinhua

This news ((Journalist Sun Jae) Yesterday evening, the NSE announced that after the approval of the China Securities Regulatory Commission (CSRC), the Beijing Stock Exchange financing securities trading business will be officially launched on February 13th, at which time the stock companies that have obtained the license to finance the BSE can be commissioned by the investors to declare the financial financial transactions to the North Exchange.
The first list of 56 stocks in the index is set to be calculated on 31 January 2023 as the benchmark date.

According to the BSE, the list of stocks and collateralized debt securities will be made public through the disclosure of financial information on the official website of the stock exchange, which will facilitate investors' inquiries.
Financing bonds are an important fundamental system in the securities market and a more mature form of trading on the international stock market.
On 2 September last year, on the occasion of the one-year anniversary of its establishment, the NEC opened a public inquiry into the financing of securities.

The launch of the BSE's financing of securities trading is an important step in continuing to advance the construction of a market system, improve the trading mechanism, and enhance the pricing function of secondary markets.

The financing of securities is conducive to enriching investors' trading strategies, meeting the needs of investors for diversified trading, promoting market price discovery and further enhancing market liquidity.

In the next step, under the leadership of the Securities and Exchange Commission of China, the NEC will continue to do its best to ensure that the securities finance business is guided by the needs of investors to enrich the trading system tools, improve the supporting mechanisms, and focus on building a first-class exchange for innovative small and medium-sized enterprises.
East Germany's last communist prime minister dies today
The successor of the Communist Party of East Germany, Hans Modrow, died last night at the age of 95, the party reported in a statement.
As a result, our party has lost an important leader.
Oh, my God.
On 13 November 1989, four days after the opening of the Berlin Wall, which had separated East and West Berlin for 28 years, Moderro said he would help transform East Germany into a democratic state.
At the time, the Communist Party leaders were forced to step down as protesters across East Germany demanded democracy and freedom.
hallucination
After the Soviet Union came to power, Mikhail Gorbachev called for changes in Soviet-dominated Eastern Europe as well.
In March 1990, Modro proclaimed the first and only free elections in the German Democratic Republic (GDR).
The results of the elections led him to no longer serve as prime minister.
Despite his reforms, Modro's opponents accused him of trying to delay the political change and unification that took place in October 1990.
He has also been criticized for trying to reform the secret police instead of abolishing it.
In 1993, Modro was convicted of electoral fraud in the May 1989 municipal elections, but did not go to jail.
Some say the accusations are politically motivated.
From 1990 to 1994, Moderro continued to serve in the German parliament and was a member of the European Parliament from 1999 to 2004.
Modro sees himself as a reformer and wants to change the Communist Party from within.
In 1999, he told Reuters that he did not want the former East Germany to return, but that it should be recognized for its achievements.
Modro was born in 1928 in what was then the German town of Jasenitz (now Jasienica, Poland) and trained as a mechanic.

During World War II, he served as head of a youth fire brigade and soon after the conflict ended as a member of the Volkssturm, a Nazi militia organization that recruited men between the ages of 16 and 60 to fight in the final war struggles.
At the age of 17, Modro was captured by Soviet troops and taken as a prisoner of war to the Soviet Union, where he attended an anti-fascist course and became a staunch Communist Party member.
In 1949, the year East Germany was founded, he returned home to find a job as a mechanic and continued his studies in social sciences and economics, obtaining a doctorate.

Moderro was a staff member of the Free German Youth movement, to which almost all East German youth joined, and was promoted to chairman of Dresden's regional party through the ruling Socialist Unity Party (SED) between 1973 and 1989.
He also served in the East German parliament for more than 30 years.
In 1990, Moder became the de facto leader of East Germany, holding the highest state office.

Policy changes and trends
Most jurisdictions that have legalized cannabis for non-medical use have a growing trend of cannabis use
Eleven jurisdictions in Canada, Uruguay and the United States allow the manufacture of cannabis products for non-medical use.
In most of these jurisdictions, cannabis use has increased since legalization, although similar trends have been observed in other areas that have not legalized non-medical use of cannabis.

In Colorado and Washington, two of the earliest states to pass legislation, non-medical marijuana use among adults has increased, especially in the past month, and daily or nearly daily use has surpassed the national average since 2012.
All indicators show that cannabis use in Uruguay has increased since 2011, almost doubling in the last month.
This suggests that the main reason for the increase is the frequent and regular use of cannabis.
Short-term data from Canada also showed that legal market expansion in 2018-2019 was accompanied by an increase in usage.
However, in 2019, 40% of cannabis users still obtained some products from illegal sources.
Is the legalization of cannabis the reason behind the plunge in the global supply of marijuana strawberries?
In 2018, global production of cannabis strawberries fell to its lowest level in 20 years, driven by a decline in North American production, which fell by 84% over the past decade.

In comparison, cannabis seizures in the rest of the world nearly doubled over the same period. The pattern of seized cannabis suggests that policies aimed at opening up the cannabis market played a key role in its decline.
Regulations on novel psychoactive substances appear to have a deterrent effect and it is still difficult to assess the effects of domestic regulation of novel psychotropic substances.
Several countries with different regulatory regimes for new psychoactive substances show different prevalence rates of use of these substances.
In other countries, the use of new psychoactive substances has decreased following the adoption of domestic legislation.

Disadvantaged groups face harms from the market for legal and illegal drugs. The distribution of opioids for pain management and palliative care is uneven across regions, mainly in high-income countries.
In 2018, more than 90% of all prescription opioids available for medical use were in high-income countries.
About 50% in North America, 40% in Europe, and 2% in Oceania.
These countries account for about 12% of the world's population.
It is estimated that 88% of the world's population lives in low- and middle-income countries, but less than 10% consume pharmaceutical opioids.
Barriers to access to the pharmaceutical opioid class are linked to many factors, including legislation, culture, health systems and prescription practices.
Poorer people are at greater risk of developing a substance use disorder, with an estimated 35.6 million people suffering from drug addiction in 2018.

Poverty, limited education and social marginalization may increase the risk of drug use disorder and exacerbate its consequences. Research in high-income countries has confirmed this, and in these studies, an individual's socioeconomic trajectory is not only related to their condition at a given point in time, but also to a drug-use risk.

Drug use disorders also exacerbate socio-economic disadvantages, further increasing the risk of unemployment, poverty and homelessness, thereby fueling a vicious cycle of deprivation. These outcomes may also be related to demeaning attitudes and consequences within the criminal justice system.

Women, ethnic minorities and migrants, sexually diverse groups, people displaced by armed conflict or disaster, and people in rural areas may also be severely affected by substance use disorders or have difficulty accessing treatment services.

According to the Disability Adjusted Life Years (DALY) indicator, which estimates the number of years of healthy life lost to disability and premature death, the effects of harmful drug use on the broader society have increased over the past decade.
Between 2007 and 2018, the number of disability-adjusted life years attributed to drug use increased by 17% globally.
The associated disability of liver cancer caused by untreated hepatitis C, which is common among injecting drug users, was particularly high, with an increase in life expectancy of 40%.
The complexity of the relationship between drugs and violence makes it difficult to establish all the causal relationships between the use of psychoactive substances and the violence.
Limited global data suggest that intoxication may be a major contributing factor to homicide.
However, alcohol seems to play a greater role than drugs in violent incidents.

Although drug use can lead to crime, in some cases this link can be partially attributed to a number of intermediate factors, such as socioeconomic disadvantage and other types of adversity caused by personal risk, family environment and peer influence.
The link between drug trafficking and violence is multifaceted.
Large-scale organized criminal activity, including international drug trafficking, can be carried out in non-violent situations if there is a stable criminal structure.

In the short term, the presence and extent of violence depends not on the quantity of trafficking but on certain changes that destabilize the balance of power between organized crime groups, such as changes in the size of illegal markets, deaths or imprisonment of known criminals, and law enforcement measures that make one group weaker than another.

Increased complexity
The emergence of non-internationally regulated substances is stable, but the market for potentially dangerous new opioids is increasingly complex.
In addition to plant-based substances such as cannabis, cocaine and heroin, hundreds of synthetic drugs have been added, many of which are not under international regulation.
Approximately 500 new active substances are placed on the domestic market of the Member States each year.
Currently, most of these are stimulants, followed by synthetic cannabinoid receptor agonists and small amounts of opioids.
Although the overall amount of new psychoactive substances has stabilized, the proportions have changed.
Of the total number of new psychoactive substances identified in 2014, the opioid class accounted for only 2% but by 2018 this figure had risen to 9%.

Many of the novel opioid psychoactive substances in the class are analogues of fentanyl, whose pharmacological effects and harms have been shown to cause overdose deaths in North America and other regions, but to a lesser extent.

In North America, fentanyl is sometimes used as an adulterant for heroin and other drugs (including cocaine and methamphetamine), and sometimes in the manufacture of counterfeit pharmaceutical opioids.

Some evidence also suggests the phenomenon of the injection of new psychoactive substances in Europe: a study of discarded syringe residues in six European cities found that many syringes contained a new stimulant substance called potassium
2 The use of new psychoactive substances may become increasingly prevalent in vulnerable groups
New psychoactive substances in a single class almost never have a large market.
However, evidence from Europe suggests that synthetic cannabis is a serious problem among socially marginalized groups such as the homeless and prison inmates.
Twenty-two countries reported the use of novel psychoactive substances in prisons, most of which identified synthetic cannabinoids as a major challenge.
Regulation of precursor chemicals has forced innovators to innovate, most commonly as precursors used to synthesize drugs such as acetaminophen, methamphetamine and tetrahydrocannabinol.

Drug traffickers and drug manufacturers have been looking for alternatives not only to looser-regulated substances, but also to chemicals specifically designed to evade regulation, the so-called methylprednisolone.
Restrictive measures aimed at stopping the spread of COVID-19 are likely to further squeeze addicts who rely on precursor chemicals.

Evidence from Mexico suggests that this has become a reality: In March 2020, it was reported that a shortage of methylprednisolone precursors imported from East Asia led to a rise in the price of methylamide in Mexico and the United States.
The market is changing.
Synthetic drugs replace opioids in Central Asia and the Russian Federation
The opioid market in Central Asia and the Russian Federation seems to have changed between 2008 and 2018.
The number of opioids seized by the authorities of the Russian Federation decreased by about 80%, while the number receiving treatment for opioid use dropped significantly.
But the market for stimulants seems to be booming.
There is evidence that methylphenidate and various calcium salts, including methoxychloroquine and a-hydroxyphenylamine, are now ubiquitously available on the Russian drug market.

Russian authorities have reported a sharp increase in the number of secret processing facilities recently seized for the manufacture of various illegal drugs, more than doubling in two years to 152 in 2018.
Growth in the Afghanistan and Iraq methamphetamine markets
As early as 2012, investigations of hospital, prison and other institutional personnel revealed the importance of methamphetamine in Iraq.
Crystalline methamphetamine has become a major drug of concern, alongside ciprofloxacin and curcumin.
A 2015 study further confirmed these findings, with drug users reporting that cannabis is harder to obtain than methadone or methamphetamine.

Recently, several methamphetamine processing plants have been discovered by Iraqi authorities, and the Cannabis Regulatory Authority has expressed concern about the large-scale imports of pseudoephedrine preparations.
In Afghanistan, methamphetamine production appears to have begun in 2014.
Since then, methylphenidate seizures have been steadily increasing.
However, in the first half of 2019, the capture of 1^657 kg of tuna increased dramatically compared to the previous year.
Large quantities of methamphetamine believed to have originated in Afghanistan have been seized in other countries, indicating that production is rising rapidly in the country.
The execution summary
The impact of coronavirus on the drug market
The impact could be similar to the economic crisis of 2008.
The global COVID-19 outbreak has plunged the world into an unprecedented crisis.

In many countries, the disease has left healthcare institutions overwhelmed and on the brink of collapse, and restrictive measures put in place by governments have caused serious disruption to the global economy.
The impact of the epidemic on the drug market is unclear and difficult to predict, but it has the potential to be far-reaching.
Some producers may be forced to find new ways to manufacture drugs because restrictions on movement also restrict access to precursors and basic chemicals.
Traffickers are unable to cross the border due to travel restrictions and may have to find new routes and methods.
The patterns of drug use and supply may change, and the government's ability to respond may be hampered.
The transformation brought about by COVID-19 is unprecedented, but lessons can be learned from past crises.
Following the 2008 economic crisis, some drug users started looking for cheaper synthetic substances and switched to injectable drugs.
At the same time, governments are cutting drug-related budgets.
Interventions such as prevention of drug use and associated risk behaviors and drug treatment services could be hit hard if governments respond to the current recession in the same way.
In addition, the priority of international cooperation in interception may be reduced, making it easier for traffickers to act.
Some countries have large quantities of drugs being smuggled on commercial flights and are expected to be the countries most directly affected by drug trafficking.

Some messengers carry synthetic drugs, such as methamphetamine, in their backpacks or hidden in private luggage, sometimes in large quantities. As air passenger transportation is restricted in almost all parts of the world, the supply of drugs using commercial air travel may be completely interrupted.
Although international postal supply chains have also been disrupted, trafficking using the dark web and freight mail may increase.
In the long run, the recession and related closures could disrupt the drug market.
hallucination

As a result of rising unemployment and lack of opportunities, poor and vulnerable people will be more likely to use drugs in harmful ways, develop substance use disorders, and turn to illicit drug-related activities, whether in production or transport.
Drug trafficking organizations may take advantage of this situation to provide services to vulnerable groups and recruit new members to strengthen their ranks.
These changes could quickly take root and become a new reality for many communities as the government's capacity to respond declines.
Expansion and Complexity
Growth of the market
Population growth patterns partly explain why the market is expanding
Drug use has been on the rise around the world, both in terms of overall numbers and the proportion of drug users in the global population.
In 2009, there were an estimated 210 million drug users, or 4.8% of the global population aged 15-64, compared to 269 million or 5.3% in 2018.
Over the past two decades, drug use in developing countries has grown much faster than in developed countries.

This partly reflects the differences in the overall population growth over this period, with developed countries accounting for 7% and developing countries for 28%, but also the rapid growth of the young population in developing nations.
Teenagers and young adults account for the largest proportion of drug users.
Between 2000 and 2018, the population of this age group in developing countries grew by 16%, while that of developed countries decreased by 10%.
1 Urbanization is a driver of current and future drug markets
Drugs are more prevalent in urban areas than in rural areas, both in developed and developing countries.
Part of the reason for the overall increase in drug use is the massive migration of people from rural to urban areas, where more than half the world's population now lives, up from 34% in 1960.
Urbanization is likely to be a key factor in the future dynamics of drug markets, especially in developing countries where the trend is more pronounced.

Increased wealth is strongly associated with increased drug use, but the greatest burden of disease is borne by the poorest people worldwide, and drug abuse is more prevalent in developed countries than in developing ones.
Drugs such as cocaine are also strongly linked to the wealthier parts of the world.
Similarly, in different parts of the country, the prevalence of drug use is higher among the wealthy social classes.
However, a higher proportion of people with lower socioeconomic status convert to drug use disorder.
Data from a handful of countries suggest a link between harmful drug use patterns and morbidity and low income.
These patterns seem to be less common in wealthier sections of society.
The economic constraints caused by the global COVID-19 crisis are likely to increase the risk to the most vulnerable groups, including drug users.

For example, changes in the labor market, such as rising unemployment rates, have been linked to an increase in drug use, an epidemic that has put tens of millions of people out of work around the world.

The coronavirus pandemic may result in more farmers growing or engaging in illegal crop cultivation, or due to reduced control capacity of the national authorities or because more people may have to take risks and engage in illicit activities under the economic crisis.

The associated COVID-19 restrictions have led to a decrease in air and land traffic, which may have resulted in an increase in maritime trafficking, a lower risk of interception at sea, and a greater number of cases of smuggling than air or land.
Recently, there have been reports of cocaine shipments being shipped directly from South America to Europe by sea.
The latest trends
Smoking cannabis is the most commonly used substance, and opioids are most dangerous.
An estimated 192 million people used cannabis in 2018, making it the most widely used drug in the world.
In comparison, 58 million people used opioids in 2018.
However, the associated dangers of opioids are largely ignored due to the small number of users.
Of the estimated 167,000 drug-related deaths in 2017, 66% were caused by these substances and 50% of the 21 million years of life lost to disability or premature death believed to be due to drug use.
Non-medical use of synthetic opioids exacerbates public health crisis

In West, Central and North Africa, the opioid crisis is exacerbated by Kumado; in North America, by fentanyl. The two regions have little in common in terms of economics, demographics, or general patterns of drug use, but are struggling to combat opioids fueled by readily available and low-cost substances.
In North America, the use of synthetic opioids such as fentanyl has led to an increase in opioid overdose deaths over the past 20 years.
In 2018, two-thirds of the 67,367 overdose deaths reported in the United States were related to fentanyl.
Canada reported similar results, but with lower numbers.
Fentanyl leads to overdose deaths in part due to the unpredictability of the drug on the illicit drug market.
In West, Central and North Africa, the market for non-medical curcumin has grown significantly.
In the region, treatment for Kumamoto is increasingly being used by patients with the disease.
In 2017, the majority of horses harvested globally increased significantly, reaching a peak of over 125 tonnes.
In 2018, however, the global capture fell to 32 tonnes after India passed a new law regulating curcumin.
Both crises were fueled by the simplicity of manufacturing and the low cost of production, as well as the lack of international regulation for Kumado and many fentanyl analogues or their precursors.
Adding to both crises is the availability of these substances on both the drug and illicit markets, making them harder to detect and prevent abuse.
Increased use of stimulants
The doping sector is dominated by cocaine and methamphetamine, both of which are on the rise in their major markets.
An estimated 19 million people used cocaine in 2018, due to its popularity in North America and Western Europe.
Approximately 27 million people used acetaminophen in the same year, with methamphetamine being the most commonly used stimulant in Southeast Asia and North America.
According to most of the indicators available, the use of methamphetamine in these two regions has been expanding over the past 20 years.

In some markets, cocaine and methamphetamine can co-exist, sometimes interchangeably, with the use of one drug decreasing as that of the other increases, and sometimes increasing and declining simultaneously to meet demand in the same market.
Coronavirus puts injecting drug users at increased risk
It is estimated that about 11.3 million people injected drugs in 2018, and about 10% of the global HIV infection is due to injection drug use.
More than one million people are infected with HIV from injecting drug users and 5.5 million are living with hepatitis C.
In 2017, about 585,000 people died from drug-related deaths, half of them from hepatitis C-associated liver disease.

We looked: What do the side effects of the coronavirus vaccine mean?
• Could this indicate a stronger immune system in those who do experience these symptoms, or is it just an unfounded rumor?

While more and more people are getting vaccinated, the lack of information about side effects continues to confuse and create rumors, most of which are false. Is the immune system of those who have developed adverse reactions stronger than those whose bodies have responded less severely to the vaccine, perhaps proving that their system is unable to fight off a foreign body entering the body?

There are several levels of responses to the vaccine, says Dr. David Devere, chief of primary care at the U.S. Centers for Disease Control and Prevention and a member of the CDC's Advisory Committee on Epidemiology.
Is there a link between the levels of antibodies you develop and the side effects?

There is no correlation between feelings and the development of antibodies to the virus. About 60 to 50 percent experience side effects, but about 90 percent develop anti-virus defenses. People who develop stronger responses are not found to be more protected.

There is no correlation in the medical literature between immediate response and vaccine levels. In some trials in which people also received placebo vaccines, a quarter developed headaches. It is also a psychological factor - how the person responds to the vaccination, whether he expects side effects. Many of the side-effects could have occurred normally, but because the public is immune, it attributes the response to vaccinations themselves, and this is a misconception that we see about vaccining in general - the attribution of adverse events that occur near and attributable to it.

Medical negligence at different stages of labor
In order to win damages, the plaintiffs must prove, in addition to negligence, that the damage was caused by neglect.
Childbirth is one of the most joyous and exciting events in a family's life, but unfortunately, sometimes births end in serious birth defects or miscarriages as a result of medical negligence.

In cases where the birth ended with a physical injury, to the child or the mother, there is room for examination of the sequence of events that resulted in the injury and even for considering seeking legal advice. A lawyer specializing in medical malpractice will examine whether there were defects in conduct by the medical staff at the various stages of birth that caused the damage and, where appropriate, seek the advice of a medical expert in a relevant field.

It should be emphasized that not every medical error amounts to negligence (in the legal sense of the term) and that various complications during childbirth do not necessarily teach that the procedure was negligent. When, then, is the case?
In this article, we will examine the different stages of childbirth, explain what complications may occur at each stage and when they amount to medical negligence.
The axis phase

At this stage, the cervix gradually opens (to allow the passage of the fetus at birth) and at the end the process should reach a diameter of about ten centimeters. Most cases of medical negligence during the incision stage involve the failure to identify fetal distress towards birth, which causes damage to the unborn child, sometimes manifested even in cerebral palsy.
Cerebral palsy:

Cerebral palsy may be caused by a lack of recognition or delay in the detection of a subconjunctival aspiration, which is manifested by failure to supply oxygen to the fetus' brain tissue. Generally, monitoring the condition of the newborn and correctly decoding the monitor monitoring fetal heart activity should lead to early identification of development of foetal distress, allowing the medical team to act quickly and rescue the infant before it is irreversibly injured. Cases in which medical staff ignore indications that the foetus suffers from a deficiency in prognosis or the team incorrectly interprets the data in its possession and in particular the working monitor or a response to a finding in a hospital for the prevention of malnutrition.

Cerebral palsy can also be caused by a fall from the umbilical cord and by an unidentified rupture of the uterus. Even in these severe cases, it is important to determine whether the medical team acted appropriately.

For example, attorney Anna Reif Ligenza, of the financial firm Cerro & Co., which specializes in representing medical malpractice victims, relates that her office handled a lawsuit of a child who was injured during birth after the midwife kicked the umbilical sac when the fetal head was too high, thereby causing a falling cord (when the cord precedes the baby's head) and impaired oxygen supply to the foetal brain (as a result of pressure from the brain on the navel cord), resulting in a baby being born with severe neurological damage.

The active stage of labor
The active stage of labor begins when the opening of the cervix reaches a diameter of 4 inches [10 cm] and ends with the birth of a baby.
Pregnancy and the Avoidance of C-section

In some cases, a dysfunctional birth develops, which is the lack of progression of the active birth process. In such cases a caesarean section is usually performed, in order to prevent various damages that may be caused to the fetus due to delayed birth.

There are instances where failure to perform a cesarean on time can cause irreversible harm to the fetus, explained attorney Rafe-Lingenza. "For example, we have handled a medical malpractice case involving the death of a newborn resulting from a significant delay in having a caesarian.
Carelessly giving birth to a vacuum

In situations where there is a significant danger to the mother or fetus requiring a particularly rapid termination of labor, a vacuum delivery is sometimes performed. This process involves placing a "dope" on the foetus's head and forcibly pulling it out. Naturally, this action is hazardous and can cause harm to both the embryo and the woman giving birth and therefore requires great care, precision, and skill.

In these cases, medical negligence may be manifested by the physician not following the mandatory guidelines and performing the operation despite the existence of a contraindication, such as when the fetal head is too high in the pelvis, or performs it for too long or when despite several failed attempts the doctor continues and repeats the procedure more than the allowed number of times.
Paralysis in the name of ERB

Paralysis is caused by congenital nerve damage to the brachial plexus (a network of nerves that connects the spine and the upper part of the shoulder) and when it occurs during childbirth it is advisable to check whether the damage occurred as a result of negligence by the delivery team. The damage is manifested by weakness of muscles in the hand and can reach complete paralysus of all the arm.

When should you suspect paralysis as a result of medical negligence? In cases where a weight assessment of the fetus indicates that it is a chromosomal foetus, i.e. expected to be born weighing more than 4.5 kg and according to the guidelines, a caesarean delivery is preferable. When the child's weight is greater than 4 kg, Caesarian should be considered in light of risk factors including gestational diabetes and the length of second stage of labor.

Indeed, in 2694/90 B.C.E., the Supreme Court ruled that "the risk of shoulder formation during birth can be predicted in advance with some degree of accuracy, and the way to prevent the formation, where it is likely to occur, is by cesarean section".
Exit phase of the placenta

The separation of the placenta from the uterus and its exit occurs due to the contraction of a womb after the delivery and is accompanied by bleeding. The process usually lasts for up to half an hour from when the baby is delivered and often happens spontaneously, without the involvement of medical staff.

During this stage, complications can occur that can cause serious damage to the fetus. One known complication due to uterine fibroids is called "Ashman's syndrome", the abnormal scarring of the womb resulting from inflammation caused by excessive fibrosis, a phenomenon that affects the cervix in a way that does not allow the pregnancy to proceed.
Death at birth
In these cases, the event that was supposed to bring happiness and joy to the whole family turns, unfortunately, into the most tragic event for it.

For example, attorney Reif-Lingenza told us, "our firm filed a case involving the death of a newborn, where in that case the medical staff ignored and failed to respond to the worrisome vital signs of the birth, for long hours, and delayed the diagnosis of massive and uncontrollable bleeding that occurred as a known complication of her underlying disease".

Loss of uterus

In serious cases, medical negligence at birth can lead to a hysterectomy, says lawyer Rafe Lingeza: "Our firm filed a lawsuit against a hospital on the grounds that it removed a uterus because of medical malpractice after childbirth. In that case, the woman, a 31-year-old, lost her womb due to inadequate treatment of massive bleeding observed by the medical team after birth and yet no timely action was taken to prevent the damage".
What are the compensation claims for medical negligence in childbirth?

Childbirth compensation for injury due to medical negligence at birth includes many damage components, with the most significant amounts being for pain and suffering, nursing and wage treatment, loss of wages and pensions to the victim and even to his parents and other damages. A large scientific study recently published in the scientific journal Nature examined the impact of video conferences on the creativity of participants, compared to face-to-face meetings.

The question of the study -- led by Melanie Brooks, an assistant professor at Columbia University -- was whether computer-based remote meetings preserve the creativity that occurs in office brainstorming meetings, or whether the level of creative and free-thinking decreases as a result of distance.

People in a face-to-face meeting move around a room, use objects, and help them think creatively, says Brooks. "In a computer meeting, by contrast, the focus on maintaining eye contact with others comes at the expense of creative activity in the brain.

To test the results of the experiment and see if they repeated themselves, they were tested twice -- once at Columbia University and once in real life -- on engineers who knew each other from early acquaintances.

At the university, the researcher divided a group of 602 faculty and students into two parts: one asked the subjects to meet in person and develop solutions to a problem, and the other asked them to do so via a computer. Simultaneously, 1,490 engineers from five countries in Europe, Middle East and South Asia were asked to divide in a similar way and solve a newly presented problem. In both cases, a decrease in creativity and out-of-the-box thinking was found among those who met virtually via video.
Jay Olson, a postdoctoral fellow at McGill University in Canada and a researcher on ways to measure creativity, was not involved in the study but wasn't surprised by the results.

State inspector's report: the actual budget for most years of operation of the pharmaceutical basket committee  less than the recommended budget

According to the report by Methanieu Angelmann, for more than 20 years of Basket activity  the Ministry of Health has not supervised the activities of the Committee • The report also states that the minutes of meetings are published significantly late, if at all • Also, the critic recommends to increase the transparency of subcommittee activity and update the procedures for Basket work • Another deficiency found concerns the fact that since the committee began its activities, Health Ministry did not ask the hospital boards to report on the volume of use and utilization of drugs in Basket which would have allowed to analyze and control the budget that can be used

The Drug Basket Committee is one of the most influential public committees on our daily lives and our health. Each year, the committee decides on new drugs to be given to the public free of charge through health insurance funds but a new state inspector's report released today (Tuesday) warns that it has been operating for more than 20 years without audit reports and without the Ministry of Health and the Health Council overseeing and examining its activities.
Israel Today columnist Ren Resnick adds that the State Auditor's investigation was conducted in the wake of the ongoing exposures in "Israel Today" of drug cart manufacturers.

According to the report by Methanjo Angelmann, he recommends "to make corrections and improvements in the basket expansion process, which will lead to a more qualitative extraction of the healthcare basket budget to which the public is entitled". Throughout the years that the mechanism has been in existence, eight billion shekels of drugs were added into the state budget in 2021-1998, with the surplus moving annually in amounts ranging from 0 to 500 million.

In 2019, 2020 and 2021, requests were made to add about 800 new medicines and technologies to the health services basket, at a total annual cost of more than NIS two billion. In practice, the budget allocated for the expansion of the basket was less than the scope of applications.

The critic notes that the amount of the annual surcharge needs to be reviewed and adjusted in order to allow for certainty and long-term planning. Angelman also noted that "the transparency model in basketball work is lacking". For example, the basketball committee's working procedure stipulates that minutes of meetings, which are closed to the public, be published within 60 days, but in practice minutes are published 160-109 days late, with sometimes final meeting minutes not published at all.

Of the thousands of submissions, only one financial comment was submitted.

Another criticism of Angelman concerns a preliminary procedure for evaluating technologies submitted to the drug basket. The reviewer found that half (46%) of the submitted technologies did not pass this stage, but the Ministry of Health does not publish the reasons for the rejection.

Another deficiency concerns the activity of the Subcommittee on the Medicine Basket, which is closed to the media and the public, and where patient numbers and drug costs are discussed. The reviewer recommends that a public representative be included or that the discussions be made public without confidential commercial details.

For example, requests to add anti-obesity drugs to the basket for the 2021-2019 discussions of the Basket Committee were made. The report found that the applications were not accompanied by economic estimates, including an estimate of how much could have been saved by reducing the harm of diseases caused by obesity or by being able to avoid gastric bypass surgery.

It also arises that the decisions of the drug basket committee are not in line with the goals and strategy of Ministry of Health. For example, in 2019, the ministry of health defined cancer prevention and preparation medicine for the treatment of chronic diseases as targets, but the decision on the expansion of basket did not emphasize the need to achieve these goals.

The reviewer also warns that since 2011 the medicine basket also includes non-hospital insurance services, including various rehabilitation and mobility devices and vaccines, provided by the Ministry of Health ("Third Supplement"). This is when the legal framework for this step is regulated only in retrospect. In the last six years, NIS 74 million from the supplement to the drug basket has been used for these services.

Angelmann recommends that the Ministry of Health update the basket working procedures and also determine whether a separate financial supplement is needed for these services. About one-third of the new drugs entering the medicine basket are designated as "no-cost drugs", the use of which does not cost patients an additional amount because they replace existing treatment. The reviewer suggests examining the possibility of these drugs being prescribed in a different and shortened route so that prescriptions can be updated several times a year rather than just once per year.
There's no control over the use of very expensive drugs.

Delays in testing may lead to difficulties in data collection and analysis, irrelevance of conclusions after such a long time, subcommittee bias and decisions based on incomplete findings, the report said.

Also, the Ministry does not monitor and supervise the use of particularly expensive medicines and has not produced samples. These are 10 drugs that accounted for 62% of the addition to the basket (NIS 1.7 billion in 2021-2016).
